{"questionId":"33268148","questionHtml":"<p>Prove that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>≡</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>≠</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use identity&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≡</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>A</mi><mo> </mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to write their RHS in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>multiply through by the conjugate of the denominator <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><msup><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><msup><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to write&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math> in terms of sin and cos:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>attempt to use both sin and cos addition formulae:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>M1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mi>cos</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo> </mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mi>sin</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo> </mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>+</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>multiply through by the conjugate of the denominator <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use given identity&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≡</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>A</mi><mo> </mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>multiply through by the conjugate of the denominator&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced></mfrac><mo>·</mo><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mtext>sec</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>attempt to write their RHS in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mro